spanishExample: Toma esto y llévalo contigo a la fiesta.
englishTranslation: Take this and bring it with you to the party.

spanishExample: Tomó su teléfono y lo llevó a ese lugar bello.
englishTranslation: He took his phone and brought it to that beautiful place.

spanishExample: ¡Tranquila! Solo necesitamos el largo de la cama.
englishTranslation: (f) Calm down! We just need the length of the bed.

spanishExample: ¡Tranquilo! No puedes tomar eso, ya has tomado dieciocho.
englishTranslation: Calm down(m)! You can’t take that, you’ve already taken eighteen.

spanishExample: ¿Quieres llevar el resto contigo? Es bello.
englishTranslation: Do you want to take the rest with you? It’s beautiful.

spanishExample: Si llevas dieciséis, yo llevo el resto y será perfecto.
englishTranslation: If you take sixteen, I take the rest and it’ll be perfect.

spanishExample: Conoció a diecinueve amigos nuevos en ese lugar hermoso.
englishTranslation: He met nineteen new friends in that gorgeous place.

spanishExample: Cuando los conociste, eran lindos.
englishTranslation: When you met them, they were cute.

spanishExample: El pobre chico no conocía a su familia.
englishTranslation: The poor boy didn’t know his family.

spanishExample: Ella cree que es gracioso cuando él toma café.
englishTranslation: She thinks it is funny when he drinks coffee.

spanishExample: Es extraño que el orden no sea perfecto.
englishTranslation: It’s strange that the order isn’t perfect.

spanishExample: Este es el lugar más bonito que he conocido.
englishTranslation: This is the prettiest place I’ve known.

spanishExample: La gente ahí es pobre, pero el lugar es hermoso.
englishTranslation: The people there are poor, but the place is gorgeous.

spanishExample: La mitad de las personas fueron extrañas y la otra mitad graciosas.
englishTranslation: Half of the people were strange and the other half funny.

spanishExample: Lo conocí ayer y de verdad quería conocerlo.
englishTranslation: I met him yesterday and I really wanted to meet him.

spanishExample: No lo conoces, por eso no quiero que tome nada contigo.
englishTranslation: You don’t know him, that’s why I don’t want him to drink anything with you.

spanishExample: No me conoce, pero quiero que me conozca.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t know me, but I want her to know me.

spanishExample: No me conocen y por eso se vuelven locos.
englishTranslation: They don’t know me and that’s why they’re going crazy.

spanishExample: No tuvimos ninguna baja esta semana, eso es perfecto.
englishTranslation: We didn’t have any losses this week; that’s perfect.

spanishExample: Quiere conocerte porque nosotros te conocemos.
englishTranslation: She wants to meet you because we know you.

spanishExample: Quiero conocer un lugar bonito.
englishTranslation: I want to know a pretty place.

spanishExample: ¡Mira esta foto! ¡Qué lindo!
englishTranslation: Look at this picture! How cute!
